
Overview of adj lazy

The adj lazy has 2 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                            
1. (4) lazy -- (moving slowly and gently; "up a lazy river"; "lazy white clouds"; "at a lazy pace")
2. (2) faineant, indolent, lazy, otiose, slothful, work-shy -- (disinclined to work or exertion; "faineant kings under whose rule the country languished"; "an indolent hanger-on"; "too lazy to wash the dishes"; "shiftless idle youth"; "slothful employees"; "the unemployed are not necessarily work-shy")
